<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Clyde lifts yr shr, declares div.</title>
<headline>Clyde lifts yr shr, declares div.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended February 28</p>
<p>		     (million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, (cts)		   8.5	vs    5.6</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		   1.25	vs    nil</p>
<p>    Attrib income	     1.49	vs    0.98</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		     2.71	vs    1.89</p>
<p>    Tax			   1.16	vs    0.85</p>
<p>    Interest paid	     1.87	vs    2.03</p>
<p>    Turnover		  119.89	vs    135.03</p>
<p>Div payable June 30</p>
<p>on register June 6</p>
<p>Full name: Clyde Industrial Corporation Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said it was confident that by continuing its policy of rationalisation and improving credit control, income for the current year would be substantially better.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
</text>
